sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser
    participant Django as Django (WSGI)
    participant OTelSDK as OTel SDK
    participant Celery as Celery Task
    participant S3 as S3 / boto3
    participant Collector as OTel Collector
    participant Backend as Trace Backend<br/>(Jaeger / Tempo / Honeycomb)

    Browser->>Django: POST /flows/run/
    activate Django
    OTelSDK->>OTelSDK: Start root span<br/>service=web, http.method=POST

    Django->>Django: Validate form, create FlowExecution
    OTelSDK->>OTelSDK: Child span: db.query INSERT

    Django->>Celery: run_pipeline_task.delay(run_id)<br/>W3C traceparent header injected into task headers
    deactivate Django

    activate Celery
    OTelSDK->>OTelSDK: Extract traceparent → continue root trace<br/>Start span: celery.task run_pipeline_task

    Celery->>S3: boto3.put_object (upload input file)
    OTelSDK->>OTelSDK: Child span: http.client PUT s3://...

    Celery->>Celery: Run doit pipeline (subprocess)
    OTelSDK->>OTelSDK: Child span: subprocess.run doit

    Celery->>S3: boto3.get_object (read output)
    OTelSDK->>OTelSDK: Child span: http.client GET s3://...

    Celery->>Celery: Update FlowExecution status
    OTelSDK->>OTelSDK: Child span: db.query UPDATE

    OTelSDK->>OTelSDK: End celery task span
    deactivate Celery

    OTelSDK->>Collector: Export spans (OTLP/gRPC batch)
    Collector->>Backend: Forward traces

    note over OTelSDK,Collector: Dev: SimpleSpanProcessor (synchronous)<br/>Staging/Prod: BatchSpanProcessor (async, low overhead)
    note over Collector,Backend: Dev: Jaeger (localhost:16686)<br/>Staging: stdout JSON<br/>Prod: Tempo / Honeycomb / X-Ray (env var)
